  "metadata": {
    "fn_id": "taiwan_military_pressure",
    "note": "Scope is centroid_ids={ASIA-TAIWAN} only (~2k titles/180d), which acts as the gate the way primary_target does on Archetype-A FNs: domain verbs (drill, patrol, blockade) are cross-filtered by the Taiwan centroid and are therefore safe here, whereas they would leak across 23k ASIA-CHINA / 129k AMERICAS-USA titles under the old scope. Merged kinetic + grey-zone coercion per approved structure. Carrier names (Shandong/Fujian/Liaoning) OMITTED: all three are Chinese province names and would match province stories; 'aircraft carrier' covers the phenomenon. Bare 'PLA' is safe via the <=4-char all-caps acronym path (case-sensitive whole-word), which will not match 'plan'/'place'. Bare 'deter' DROPPED after audit: the EN path is a word-START prefix match, so it caught 'Trump and Xi will not DETERmine Taiwan's fate' -- replaced by 'deterrence'/'deterrent'.",
    "archetype": "bilateral within a single-centroid scope; primary_target null"
  },
